WEBVTT

00:01.167 --> 00:02.668
<i>Previously on</i> reign...

00:02.670 --> 00:04.069
I wanted a different life,

00:04.071 --> 00:05.537
Things you could
never give me.

00:05.539 --> 00:07.239
Then there is no reason
for me to be here.

00:07.241 --> 00:08.374
I have a feeling
I've just begun to learn

00:08.376 --> 00:09.541
The extent of your skills.

00:09.543 --> 00:10.542
General renaude.

00:10.544 --> 00:13.412
General... Is it?

00:13.414 --> 00:16.315
Catherine, I care about you.

00:17.784 --> 00:19.351
2,000 french soldiers
to scotland

00:19.353 --> 00:21.587
Means fewer soldiers
facing England,

00:21.589 --> 00:23.322
Less on our borders
with navarre,

00:23.324 --> 00:24.723
The italian
and german territories.

00:24.725 --> 00:26.625
And those are just
our foreign threats.

00:26.627 --> 00:30.129
How can I betray my husband's
wishes, endanger his country?

00:30.131 --> 00:32.131
I have ordered
2,000 french troops

00:32.133 --> 00:34.433
To sail to scotland.
France can withstand

00:34.435 --> 00:36.035
<i>A temporary absence of troops.</i>

00:36.037 --> 00:39.405
I can't leave now, louis.
What do you see now?

00:39.407 --> 00:41.540
An affair under your husband's
roof and nothing more?

00:41.542 --> 00:43.042
That's all I can offer you.

00:47.380 --> 00:49.581
(boys' choir singing in latin)

00:55.055 --> 00:57.656
(singing in latin)

00:57.658 --> 01:00.726
(men shouting)

01:00.728 --> 01:02.194
(yelling and grunting)

01:12.772 --> 01:15.441
(singing continues)

01:18.745 --> 01:21.113
(priest gasping)

01:23.783 --> 01:26.285
(cawing)

01:30.223 --> 01:33.292
(wind whistling)

01:38.198 --> 01:40.632
Louis, you're back.

01:40.634 --> 01:44.103
I was starting to worry
you'd given up on us.

01:44.105 --> 01:46.572
I went home to my region.

01:46.574 --> 01:48.807
I needed time and distance
from you to think.

01:48.809 --> 01:50.476
I know I promised you
so much more

01:50.478 --> 01:52.644
When we were going to scotland,
but I can't leave.

01:52.646 --> 01:55.547
Not when francis has
sent so many troops

01:55.549 --> 01:57.382
To defend my country, my throne.

01:57.384 --> 01:59.585
Oh, you had
to protect your crown, mary.

01:59.587 --> 02:01.320
You did the right thing.

02:01.322 --> 02:02.721
And what about you?

02:02.723 --> 02:04.823
Did I do right by you?

02:07.160 --> 02:10.329
You offered me an affair
in the home of your husband.

02:10.331 --> 02:13.332
I'm offering you <i>me...</i> My love.

02:13.334 --> 02:15.400
These last few weeks
without you...

02:15.402 --> 02:19.238
I felt as though I was dying.

02:21.474 --> 02:23.475
Louis...

02:23.477 --> 02:25.344
Did you come here
to say good-bye?

02:25.346 --> 02:27.913
Or did you hope
that I would?

02:27.915 --> 02:29.681
Because that's not what I want.

02:31.184 --> 02:33.185
I love you.

02:33.187 --> 02:35.487
And I want us to be together.

02:44.531 --> 02:46.698
(horse neighing)

02:46.700 --> 02:48.500
Riding again?

02:48.502 --> 02:49.635
So soon after your injury?

02:49.637 --> 02:51.303
I've healed quickly.

02:51.305 --> 02:52.771
It brings me peace,

02:52.773 --> 02:54.173
Being out in the woods.

02:54.175 --> 02:56.642
You mean, being alone.

02:56.644 --> 02:59.178
I know that this has been
hard on you, too,

02:59.180 --> 03:01.547
Our separation,
but to see you flee

03:01.549 --> 03:04.516
An entire castle just
to avoid being around me...

03:04.518 --> 03:06.185
You needn't worry.
But I do.

03:06.187 --> 03:08.754
I don't want to see you
suffer on my account.

03:08.756 --> 03:09.821
I'm fine, really.

03:09.823 --> 03:12.191
Recovering in all ways.

03:12.193 --> 03:14.293
Well, then, why are you spending
all of your days in the woods?

03:14.295 --> 03:16.562
There's a friend that I've
been passing time with--

03:16.564 --> 03:17.963
Fishing, hunting.

03:17.965 --> 03:19.731
But you don't have any friends.

03:19.733 --> 03:21.934
You have people
you're bound to--

03:21.936 --> 03:24.269
Your brother, me...

03:25.438 --> 03:27.206
Who is this friend?

03:27.208 --> 03:28.640
It's no one you know.

03:28.642 --> 03:32.411
Well, does this <i>friend</i>
<i>have a name?</i>

03:32.413 --> 03:34.880
Breasts? A vagina?

03:34.882 --> 03:36.448
Stop! Yes. Yes, to both.

03:36.450 --> 03:37.983
None of your business,

03:37.985 --> 03:39.985
As your doings
are none of mine.

03:39.987 --> 03:40.953
My lord,

03:40.955 --> 03:43.222
We need you immediately.

03:46.993 --> 03:48.427
Protestant rebels
have seized

03:48.429 --> 03:49.928
The benedictine monastery
outside angers.

03:49.930 --> 03:52.598
There are at least a dozen
of them, heavily armed.

03:52.600 --> 03:53.932
They've rounded up
the children,

03:53.934 --> 03:55.434
Killed all the guards
and the monks.

03:55.436 --> 03:56.835
Oh, my god.

03:56.837 --> 03:57.936
Save two who managed to escape.

03:57.938 --> 03:59.504
I just heard.

03:59.506 --> 04:00.939
How many are dead?

04:00.941 --> 04:03.308
At least 40. 19 hostages.

04:03.310 --> 04:04.977
If the boys are still alive.

04:04.979 --> 04:06.011
Francis:
Children.

04:06.013 --> 04:07.346
What are these radicals doing?

04:07.348 --> 04:08.714
Ransoming them, or do they plan

04:08.716 --> 04:10.249
To slaughter them, as well?

04:10.251 --> 04:11.383
It's further retaliation for

04:11.385 --> 04:12.484
Sending our troops
into scotland.

04:12.486 --> 04:13.852
For supporting me,
a catholic queen.

04:13.854 --> 04:15.754
I knew that there would be
consequences.

04:15.756 --> 04:17.689
France had
to honor its alliance.

04:17.691 --> 04:19.691
Francis, the parents,
some of the local nobles

04:19.693 --> 04:22.327
Are beginning to gather
to meet with us.

04:22.329 --> 04:26.031
(bell tolling in distance)

04:26.033 --> 04:29.034
Has general savoy
and his men returned?

04:29.036 --> 04:31.770
He's still in scotland
doing another advance sweep,

04:31.772 --> 04:32.838
In the borderlands.

04:32.840 --> 04:35.340
We'll put together
a team from the castle,

04:35.342 --> 04:36.975
As many soldiers
as we can spare.

04:36.977 --> 04:38.744
These men aren't trained
for that type of mission.

04:38.746 --> 04:40.612
Extracting children
from an armed assault.

04:40.614 --> 04:41.980
The boys could die in the melee.

04:41.982 --> 04:44.850
Prepare them anyway,
as a last resort.

04:50.923 --> 04:53.425
What are you doing
to save our sons?

04:54.994 --> 04:57.296
We are sending envoys to
negotiate their release,

04:57.298 --> 04:59.564
And if that fails,
we will secure

04:59.566 --> 05:01.466
The safest possible
route to rescue them.

05:01.468 --> 05:03.802
This scum would
never have dared

05:03.804 --> 05:04.936
To take our sons hostage,

05:04.938 --> 05:07.472
Or kill men of god,
if our army were here.

05:07.474 --> 05:08.974
(group murmuring)
count, watch your tongue.

05:08.976 --> 05:12.444
I know that you fear
for the life of your son,

05:12.446 --> 05:14.579
But you are addressing
your sovereign king.

05:16.516 --> 05:19.551
These rebels will be
captured and hanged,

05:19.553 --> 05:21.486
And I will do everything
in this nation's power

05:21.488 --> 05:23.021
To return your sons
to you safely.

05:23.023 --> 05:24.656
Mary:
We know there is nothing

05:24.658 --> 05:26.558
More precious to you
than your children,

05:26.560 --> 05:30.462
And we will defend them
as if they were our own.

05:30.464 --> 05:33.699
Come, let us leave the king
to attend to your sons.

05:33.701 --> 05:36.568
(murmuring)

05:37.670 --> 05:39.738
(sighs)

05:41.708 --> 05:42.908
What's wrong?

05:42.910 --> 05:45.711
Those poor boys
must be terrified,

05:45.713 --> 05:47.479
Trapped by violent men,

05:47.481 --> 05:48.980
Not knowing if they're
going to die.

05:48.982 --> 05:51.116
You can't even imagine, francis.

05:51.118 --> 05:53.985
We will save them.

05:53.987 --> 05:56.655
And you are safe...
Here with me.

05:59.559 --> 06:02.027
Man (in distance):
Welcome back, my lord!

06:08.735 --> 06:10.569
Conde:
Follow me.
I...

06:10.571 --> 06:11.903
Man (in distance):
To your chambers, my lord?

06:11.905 --> 06:14.072
I was coming to
tell you that

06:14.074 --> 06:15.741
CondÃ© had returned to court.

06:15.743 --> 06:17.976
He was gone for weeks.

06:17.978 --> 06:21.079
I'm sorry
if you thought it was over.

06:21.081 --> 06:24.082
Well... You were planning

06:24.084 --> 06:27.152
To abandon our marriage,
flee France

06:27.154 --> 06:28.987
And run off
with my cousin, so...

06:30.123 --> 06:31.656
...I no longer
care what you do.

06:38.598 --> 06:41.166
(fast tempo acoustic
intro playing)

06:43.836 --> 06:46.171
â™ª they all need something

06:46.173 --> 06:51.076
â™ª to hold on to,
they all mean well â™ª

06:51.078 --> 06:54.713
â™ª you could never
feel my story â™ª

06:54.715 --> 06:58.617
â™ª it's all you know... Oh!

06:58.619 --> 07:01.787
â™ª

07:12.031 --> 07:13.698
<i>(catherine sighs)</i>

07:13.700 --> 07:18.470
Francis... He's under
so much pressure.

07:18.472 --> 07:20.906
Those poor boys
at the monastery,

07:20.908 --> 07:23.008
Shortage of troops,

07:23.010 --> 07:24.810
And now condÃ© has returned.

07:24.812 --> 07:28.213
How that bourbon continues
to keep his head, I don't know.

07:28.215 --> 07:31.082
The way that he has
taken advantage of mary

07:31.084 --> 07:33.685
At such a vulnerable time.

07:33.687 --> 07:35.120
Vulnerable? How?

07:36.789 --> 07:38.156
It doesn't matter.

07:38.158 --> 07:40.158
Every time I see him

07:40.160 --> 07:41.760
I want to tear him to pieces,

07:41.762 --> 07:43.595
I want to crush him in my fist.

07:43.597 --> 07:47.098
You... Are so frustrated.

07:47.100 --> 07:48.600
Oh...

07:48.602 --> 07:51.069
Well, not the least of which
because I have to endure

07:51.071 --> 07:54.539
A freezing carriage every
time I crave your touch.

07:56.776 --> 07:59.911
Well... It won't be long

07:59.913 --> 08:01.680
Before I am slipping

08:01.682 --> 08:05.650
Into your warm, royal bed.

08:05.652 --> 08:07.919
(chuckles)
I have a few ideas

08:07.921 --> 08:10.689
About my return
to court already.

08:10.691 --> 08:13.992
Do you never stop calculating?

08:13.994 --> 08:15.694
No.
Hmm?

08:15.696 --> 08:17.162
Never.
Mm.

08:17.164 --> 08:19.164
General renaude can help us

08:19.166 --> 08:20.165
With one plan.

08:20.167 --> 08:21.700
And the other...

08:21.702 --> 08:23.068
Could dispatch

08:23.070 --> 08:24.536
The prince of condÃ©
permanently.

08:24.538 --> 08:25.770
How?

08:25.772 --> 08:27.772
Are you just teasing me?

08:27.774 --> 08:29.608
It does come
with a caveat.

08:29.610 --> 08:31.276
A few men would have to die.

08:31.278 --> 08:33.712
Men die every day in France.

08:33.714 --> 08:34.746
I'm listening.

08:34.748 --> 08:36.081
I'll tell you after.

08:36.083 --> 08:38.917
I don't want you
satisfied that quickly.

08:44.123 --> 08:46.291
I can't believe bash
has already moved on.

08:46.293 --> 08:48.793
He could fall in love with
a mushroom if he had to.

08:48.795 --> 08:50.061
In love?

08:50.063 --> 08:51.730
She sounds more like
a hunting chum.

08:51.732 --> 08:53.064
She's not.

08:53.066 --> 08:54.733
You were ready
to leave bash for antoine.

08:54.735 --> 08:56.668
Do you want him back?
No.

08:56.670 --> 08:58.803
We'd still have the same
problems between us.

08:58.805 --> 09:01.740
You know, he wouldn't spend
a moment at home with me,

09:01.742 --> 09:03.141
Yet he would happily
die for a stranger,

09:03.143 --> 09:04.876
If it were for a noble cause.

09:04.878 --> 09:07.178
At least you no longer have
to feel guilty for leaving him.

09:07.180 --> 09:08.713
There is that.

09:08.715 --> 09:10.682
And besides,
I really shouldn't complain.

09:10.684 --> 09:12.717
Look at us-- we have all
the luxuries imaginable,

09:12.719 --> 09:14.953
And yet poor greer is
living god knows where.

09:14.955 --> 09:16.955
Oh, I know.

09:16.957 --> 09:19.057
The money we're taking her
should help a little bit.

09:19.059 --> 09:21.860
Whatever her new place
looks like, don't say a word.

09:23.329 --> 09:25.897
It's bound
to be ghastly.

09:28.868 --> 09:30.201
Right this way.

09:32.972 --> 09:35.607
(clears throat)
greer, how can
you afford this?

09:35.609 --> 09:37.776
And who are your
new housemates?

09:37.778 --> 09:39.744
They're not my housemates,

09:39.746 --> 09:42.814
Though, uh, they do...

09:42.816 --> 09:44.316
Live here with me.

09:44.318 --> 09:46.785
They are my workers.

09:46.787 --> 09:48.787
Working girls.

09:50.323 --> 09:51.790
(gasps anxiously)

09:51.792 --> 09:53.191
I am a madam.

09:53.193 --> 09:54.726
A what?
Uh...

09:54.728 --> 09:56.761
I suppose you could say
I fell into it.

09:56.763 --> 09:58.697
And as it turns out,

09:58.699 --> 10:00.165
I'm quite good at it.

10:00.167 --> 10:02.067
I think you're being modest.

10:02.069 --> 10:05.870
It's not the ideal vocation,
I'll admit.

10:05.872 --> 10:07.272
But it pays well,

10:07.274 --> 10:09.774
And I'm in charge of my life
for the very first time.

10:09.776 --> 10:13.111
I hope you won't judge me
too harshly for it.

10:14.080 --> 10:16.081
Greer, we love you.

10:16.083 --> 10:17.215
We want you
to be happy

10:17.217 --> 10:18.883
And taken care of.

10:18.885 --> 10:21.086
I am happy, most days.

10:21.088 --> 10:22.887
Though,
just this morning,

10:22.889 --> 10:24.789
I tried to buy damask
for some drapes

10:24.791 --> 10:26.891
And the proprietor
nearly threw me out.

10:26.893 --> 10:29.194
It turns out her husband
is a frequent visitor.

10:29.196 --> 10:30.395
Lola:
Oh, no.

10:30.397 --> 10:32.263
That's horrible.
On the other hand,

10:32.265 --> 10:33.832
My new profession does require

10:33.834 --> 10:34.899
That I have champagne
at the ready

10:34.901 --> 10:36.267
At all times.

10:36.269 --> 10:38.803
You know what I just realized?

10:38.805 --> 10:40.672
We're all basically

10:40.674 --> 10:43.742
Fallen women-- an unwed
mother, a divorcÃ©e...

10:43.744 --> 10:47.679
Eventually, and now a madam.

10:47.681 --> 10:49.714
So I say to hell with
what people think.

10:54.820 --> 10:56.187
Do it.

10:58.090 --> 11:00.959
You should be able to place them
without being seen.

11:00.961 --> 11:03.028
Complete with condÃ©'s seal.

11:03.030 --> 11:04.963
No one watches the dead.

11:14.173 --> 11:15.974
The scouts have reported back.

11:15.976 --> 11:18.309
The hostages are scattered
throughout the monastery,

11:18.311 --> 11:19.744
Making it impossible

11:19.746 --> 11:21.746
For us to rescue
all the boys at once.

11:21.748 --> 11:23.915
And there are still no demands?

11:23.917 --> 11:25.684
The radicals refuse
to make contact.

11:25.686 --> 11:27.018
That's not
the worst of it.

11:27.020 --> 11:28.420
These men have gunpowder--

11:28.422 --> 11:29.854
At least 30 barrels of it,

11:29.856 --> 11:31.256
From what our scouts could see.

11:31.258 --> 11:33.792
No, they can't...

11:33.794 --> 11:36.061
They're going to kill
themselves and the boys.

11:36.063 --> 11:39.964
If they have no demands,
what are they waiting for?

11:39.966 --> 11:41.700
They're waiting
for word to spread.

11:41.702 --> 11:42.901
The longer we fear

11:42.903 --> 11:44.335
For those boys, the stronger

11:44.337 --> 11:46.271
And more powerful
that fear becomes.

11:46.273 --> 11:47.972
Once they feel
the terror's taken hold,

11:47.974 --> 11:49.074
They'll ignite the gunpowder.

11:49.076 --> 11:50.375
Making a name for themselves,

11:50.377 --> 11:52.010
And their cause,
that we will never forget.

11:52.012 --> 11:53.978
All this because I sent troops
to scotland for you.

11:53.980 --> 11:56.881
I honored our alliance
and our marriage

11:56.883 --> 11:59.451
After what you planned
to do-- abandon me

11:59.453 --> 12:01.786
And France to run away
with your lover.

12:01.788 --> 12:02.954
Mary:
I was leaving

12:02.956 --> 12:04.956
To reclaim my country
and my throne.

12:04.958 --> 12:06.791
You would've done the same.

12:08.494 --> 12:10.995
We can't predict

12:10.997 --> 12:12.964
When their madness
will decide to end this.

12:12.966 --> 12:14.265
Those boys could die
at any minute.

12:14.267 --> 12:15.333
Well, we can't wait any longer.

12:15.335 --> 12:16.468
Take your men,

12:16.470 --> 12:17.869
And free them now.

12:17.871 --> 12:19.003
I will carry out your word.

12:19.005 --> 12:20.171
And if need be, I will gladly

12:20.173 --> 12:21.840
Lay down my life
for those children.

12:21.842 --> 12:23.007
But you should know...

12:23.009 --> 12:23.875
The men we have are not right

12:23.877 --> 12:25.176
For this mission.

12:26.746 --> 12:28.012
May god be with us.

12:57.977 --> 12:59.310
Archers ready?

12:59.312 --> 13:01.146
It'll be any moment now.

13:01.148 --> 13:03.281
(grunting)

13:04.784 --> 13:06.317
All clear.

13:06.319 --> 13:08.153
Let's go.

13:31.877 --> 13:33.478
Bash:
Something's wrong.

13:33.480 --> 13:34.946
Stop!

13:34.948 --> 13:36.114
Fall back now!

13:36.116 --> 13:38.216
Fall back!
(grunting, shouting)

13:48.494 --> 13:50.195
I cannot begin to fathom

13:50.197 --> 13:52.263
The hatred of someone
willing to hurt children.

13:52.265 --> 13:54.599
And their hatred
only incites more.

13:54.601 --> 13:57.202
Not just against the radicals,
but against all protestants.

13:57.204 --> 14:01.172
And louis; the timing for
his return couldn't be worse.

14:01.174 --> 14:03.441
What about the timing
for you and francis?

14:03.443 --> 14:04.976
Francis and I?

14:04.978 --> 14:06.411
CondÃ© left so abruptly.

14:06.413 --> 14:07.612
And you said yourself
you weren't sure

14:07.614 --> 14:09.047
Where you stood with him,

14:09.049 --> 14:11.049
Now that you're
not going to scotland.

14:11.051 --> 14:13.117
You're here. In France.

14:13.119 --> 14:14.619
With francis.

14:14.621 --> 14:17.589
Francis tolerates me
in my duty as queen.

14:17.591 --> 14:20.892
But there is nothing left
of our marriage to salvage.

14:20.894 --> 14:24.362
Do you honestly believe there's
still hope for you and condÃ©?

14:24.364 --> 14:27.298
We knew that being together
wasn't going to be easy.

14:27.300 --> 14:30.635
But louis has risked
so much for me.

14:30.637 --> 14:34.038
Mary, I understand
what he has done for you.

14:34.040 --> 14:35.306
He has helped you through

14:35.308 --> 14:38.142
A terrible, painful time.

14:38.144 --> 14:40.144
Is it possible you might

14:40.146 --> 14:42.213
Be confusing
gratitude with love?

14:42.215 --> 14:44.916
I'm not going to abandon him.

14:47.019 --> 14:49.087
Bash:
<i>The scouts reported</i>

14:49.089 --> 14:50.655
There were only two rebels
in the eastern grounds.

14:50.657 --> 14:53.091
But after the raid, they
admitted they hadn't been sure.

14:53.093 --> 14:54.559
Those boys' lives
are still at risk

14:54.561 --> 14:56.127
Because your men weren't sure?

14:56.129 --> 14:58.263
These men trained
for conflicts so large

14:58.265 --> 15:00.231
That a few men would never
turn the tides of battle.

15:00.233 --> 15:02.567
These are good soldiers, but
they were the wrong soldiers,

15:02.569 --> 15:04.469
And now three of them
are dead because of it.

15:04.471 --> 15:06.938
We knew this was a risk.
Mary: The rebels have

15:06.940 --> 15:08.172
Now been alerted.
They'll be quick

15:08.174 --> 15:10.074
To light that gunpowder
if we try again.

15:10.076 --> 15:12.043
Bash:
Yes. No one in that monastery

15:12.045 --> 15:13.344
Will survive our next mistake.

15:13.346 --> 15:16.147
Francis, general renaude
has men at the ready.

15:16.149 --> 15:18.650
They are trained
for this type of warfare.

15:18.652 --> 15:20.051
And loyal to narcisse.

15:20.053 --> 15:22.353
I wish that I
could trust narcisse.

15:22.355 --> 15:25.223
But everything that he touches
just spills more blood.

15:25.225 --> 15:26.424
I only know renaude
by reputation.

15:26.426 --> 15:28.126
He's mercenary
and ambitious,

15:28.128 --> 15:29.994
But he's good, very good.

15:32.231 --> 15:34.098
Take the offer.

15:37.336 --> 15:39.504
Bash is right.

15:39.506 --> 15:41.606
No matter
what narcisse's motives,

15:41.608 --> 15:44.208
If renaude can get
those boys out safe...

15:44.210 --> 15:45.510
He's our only option.

15:48.247 --> 15:49.247
Do it.

15:49.249 --> 15:50.415
And bring them back.

15:50.417 --> 15:52.250
Ready my horse.

15:52.252 --> 15:53.618
And send word
to general renaude.

15:55.087 --> 15:56.521
Be careful.

15:56.523 --> 15:58.256
I don't trust narcisse,
and least of all,

15:58.258 --> 15:59.524
When he's doing the right thing.

15:59.526 --> 16:02.193
I will.

16:04.163 --> 16:05.296
I saw something
at the monastery

16:05.298 --> 16:06.364
You need to know about.

16:06.366 --> 16:08.466
Bodies of some
of the radicals

16:08.468 --> 16:10.702
That died in the initial assault

16:10.704 --> 16:12.971
Were laying on the ground
just outside the gate.

16:12.973 --> 16:15.273
Some of them bore condÃ©'s crest.

16:15.275 --> 16:16.441
(sighs)

16:16.443 --> 16:18.176
Word that condÃ©'s a traitor

16:18.178 --> 16:19.644
Would spread like
wildfire, but...

16:19.646 --> 16:21.713
Why align himself
with these fanatics?

16:21.715 --> 16:23.481
He's accepted at court,
he has mary's protection,

16:23.483 --> 16:24.716
He has everything that he wants.

16:24.718 --> 16:26.351
I don't know.

16:26.353 --> 16:29.087
But while condÃ© was away,
he met with protestant leaders

16:29.089 --> 16:31.556
Who were furious with you
for sending troops to scotland.

16:31.558 --> 16:34.192
And our spies
tell us that even once

16:34.194 --> 16:37.228
Moderate protestants speak of
rebellion behind closed doors.

16:37.230 --> 16:39.197
You think condÃ© is with them?
And it's possible that,

16:39.199 --> 16:41.265
In rebellion,
condÃ© sees a path to power.

16:41.267 --> 16:42.734
If condÃ© had anything
to do with this,

16:42.736 --> 16:44.268
Nothing will keep him safe.

16:58.183 --> 16:59.617
What do we know, joubert?

16:59.619 --> 17:01.185
General renaude,
we disabled the water pumps,

17:01.187 --> 17:03.721
Forcing the radicals
to use the stream.

17:03.723 --> 17:06.090
We captured two of them,
and through interrogation,

17:06.092 --> 17:08.359
We confirmed their numbers--
24 armed men.

17:08.361 --> 17:09.594
What of the boys?

17:09.596 --> 17:11.262
The gunpowder and
most of the boys

17:11.264 --> 17:12.397
Are being held at the chapel.

17:12.399 --> 17:13.364
Other hostages are being held

17:13.366 --> 17:14.399
In the dormitories.

17:14.401 --> 17:15.400
Good work, lieutenant.

17:15.402 --> 17:17.702
Bash and I will take the chapel.

17:17.704 --> 17:19.037
Joubert, the dormitories.

17:19.039 --> 17:20.104
Move out.

17:20.106 --> 17:21.406
Several men:
Yes, sir!

17:21.408 --> 17:22.507
Man:
Move out!

17:26.412 --> 17:28.279
(boy crying quietly)

17:32.284 --> 17:34.819
(grunts)

17:37.689 --> 17:38.489
Man:
They're here!

17:48.600 --> 17:50.334
Stop him!

17:50.336 --> 17:52.136
The gunpowder!

17:52.138 --> 17:53.304
(grunts)

17:55.607 --> 17:57.542
(boys crying quietly)

18:00.379 --> 18:02.780
Take up defensive positions.
Others may be on their way.

18:02.782 --> 18:04.348
I'm going to check
on the dormitories.

18:04.350 --> 18:07.285
Go. We'll take it from here.

18:08.454 --> 18:10.488
Bash:
It's all right.

18:10.490 --> 18:12.857
You're safe.

18:14.526 --> 18:15.593
(knocking twice)

18:17.229 --> 18:19.330
Any news of the raid?
No, your grace.

18:19.332 --> 18:20.598
Lord condÃ© for you.

18:23.268 --> 18:25.336
Thank you for meeting
with me, lord condÃ©.

18:25.338 --> 18:28.506
Please inform me when you
receive news from angers.

18:33.579 --> 18:35.246
Why did you come to me
so openly?

18:35.248 --> 18:36.447
Is something wrong?

18:36.449 --> 18:37.748
One of my footmen
just informed me

18:37.750 --> 18:39.417
That some of my men
were found dead

18:39.419 --> 18:41.352
Amongst the radicals who
overtook the monastery.

18:41.354 --> 18:44.489
Louis, I'm sorry
to ask this but...

18:44.491 --> 18:46.691
I had no part in
this attack, mary.

18:46.693 --> 18:48.426
I'm not a traitor.

18:48.428 --> 18:51.129
Those bodies were planted
there to blame me.

18:51.131 --> 18:52.864
Francis can't
accuse me of treason

18:52.866 --> 18:54.532
Without also condemning you.

18:54.534 --> 18:56.134
He'll find another
way to be rid of me.

18:56.136 --> 18:57.735
Despite his personal feelings,

18:57.737 --> 19:00.438
Francis would never fabricate
evidence against you.

19:00.440 --> 19:02.440
You know I don't share
your trust in him.

19:02.442 --> 19:04.375
But even if you are right,

19:04.377 --> 19:06.477
It doesn't change anything.

19:06.479 --> 19:09.747
My enemies in court
multiply by the day.

19:09.749 --> 19:11.616
Francis and catherine hate me
for being with you.

19:11.618 --> 19:13.351
The rest hate me
for being protestant.

19:13.353 --> 19:15.520
They want my head, mary!

19:15.522 --> 19:17.522
Francis will protect you.

19:17.524 --> 19:19.590
He will see through
these false accusations.

19:19.592 --> 19:22.193
If I were francis,
I'd want me dead.

19:22.195 --> 19:24.328
But even if he's too good
a man to see it through,

19:24.330 --> 19:26.564
Then there's catherine
and her new lapdog narcisse.

19:26.566 --> 19:28.199
They'll find a way.

19:28.201 --> 19:30.368
If not this time, the next.

19:32.404 --> 19:33.471
I have to leave court.

19:33.473 --> 19:35.573
Maybe even France.

19:37.543 --> 19:41.379
Come with me to scotland.

19:41.381 --> 19:43.247
It's our last chance,

19:43.249 --> 19:44.782
The only way we can
be together, mary.

19:46.218 --> 19:49.320
I love you.

19:49.322 --> 19:52.590
But you know I can't go.

19:55.260 --> 19:57.395
Then that's it, then.

19:59.198 --> 20:01.566
I'm so sorry!

20:01.568 --> 20:02.867
I thought that our love would...

20:02.869 --> 20:04.535
Would be enough?

20:04.537 --> 20:05.870
No, you didn't.

20:05.872 --> 20:07.371
You warned me

20:07.373 --> 20:10.608
And warned me...
That you are queen.

20:13.579 --> 20:16.380
Louis, whatever you do,
you can't run.

20:16.382 --> 20:19.217
Stay until we have reclaimed
the monastery.

20:19.219 --> 20:21.686
And I will talk to francis.

20:24.223 --> 20:26.557
You gave me back my life.

20:26.559 --> 20:28.759
Now, let me save yours.

20:31.363 --> 20:33.464
All right.

20:45.611 --> 20:47.578
We cleared out
the rest of the monastery.

20:47.580 --> 20:49.747
16 men, including the chapel.

20:49.749 --> 20:51.315
Eight in the dormitories.

20:51.317 --> 20:53.918
So all the radicals
are accounted for.

20:53.920 --> 20:57.755
They killed two of the boys
in the commoners' dormitory

20:57.757 --> 20:59.824
Before we could stop them.

21:02.027 --> 21:04.662
Where's your
lieutenant joubert?

21:04.664 --> 21:05.997
Dead.

21:05.999 --> 21:07.598
Knife to the chest.

21:18.777 --> 21:21.379
You heard the rumors
about condÃ©.

21:21.381 --> 21:22.647
He had no part
of the attack.

21:22.649 --> 21:24.515
The nobles are already
calling for his head.

21:24.517 --> 21:27.518
Now that the children are safe,
I'll summon him for questioning.

21:27.520 --> 21:30.054
Those men were planted
there to implicate him.

21:30.056 --> 21:33.057
I know you are angry with me,
and you have every right to be.

21:33.059 --> 21:34.892
But don't let that
cloud your judgment.

21:34.894 --> 21:36.594
CondÃ© is innocent!

21:36.596 --> 21:38.663
You cannot know that.

21:38.665 --> 21:41.532
Two boys were killed
in the monastery.

21:41.534 --> 21:44.435
Now, I swore that I would
protect you being with condÃ©,

21:44.437 --> 21:46.904
But I will not turn a blind eye
to evidence of his involvement.

21:46.906 --> 21:49.540
I understand why you
no longer trust me,

21:49.542 --> 21:50.741
But trust what
you know of him.

21:50.743 --> 21:51.976
What I know of him?

21:53.078 --> 21:55.713
He took advantage of you

21:55.715 --> 21:57.515
When you were
at your most vulnerable.

21:57.517 --> 22:02.353
He knew the horrors that you had
endured and saw an opportunity.

22:02.355 --> 22:04.689
He stole my wife.

22:04.691 --> 22:06.691
The affair isn't condÃ©'s fault.

22:06.693 --> 22:07.858
It's mine.

22:08.927 --> 22:10.728
I turned to him
so many times.

22:10.730 --> 22:13.764
I turned to him because
I couldn't turn to you.

22:13.766 --> 22:16.600
Because the thought of coming
back to this room again,

22:16.602 --> 22:18.436
Where those men
assaulted me, I...

22:20.439 --> 22:22.907
Because the love in
your eyes made it feel

22:22.909 --> 22:25.343
Like I was drowning
in those memories,

22:25.345 --> 22:27.578
And I couldn't...

22:27.580 --> 22:30.581
I couldn't do that,
I had to survive.

22:30.583 --> 22:35.619
I cannot abandon him because
I led him down this path.

22:35.621 --> 22:37.922
CondÃ© is still the man
you thought he was.

22:37.924 --> 22:42.426
He deserves your trust,
even if I do not.

22:46.832 --> 22:49.633
I'll speak to the nobles.

22:51.002 --> 22:54.638
Contempt alone is not enough
to condemn a man.

22:54.640 --> 22:56.507
Even the contempt of a king.

22:56.509 --> 22:57.942
Thank you, francis.

22:57.944 --> 22:59.844
Thank you.

23:04.616 --> 23:07.551
Lord condÃ©.

23:07.553 --> 23:09.387
I don't believe
we're acquainted.

23:09.389 --> 23:10.788
We have mutual friends.

23:10.790 --> 23:13.624
I'm lord akers.

23:13.626 --> 23:15.793
Elizabeth's envoy.
You've received my messages.

23:15.795 --> 23:17.695
I nearly believed that
you cared more for your status

23:17.697 --> 23:20.765
At the french court
than a marriage to elizabeth.

23:20.767 --> 23:22.967
No, I-I'm still interested,

23:22.969 --> 23:24.802
But as a prince of the blood,

23:24.804 --> 23:26.804
Marrying without the consent
of my king is treason.

23:26.806 --> 23:29.707
With the discovery of your men
among the monastery radicals,

23:29.709 --> 23:31.776
Your life is
already at risk.

23:31.778 --> 23:33.878
My men were left there to stir
catholic prejudice against me.

23:33.880 --> 23:36.680
Prejudice may fan
the flames,

23:36.682 --> 23:39.784
But I believe your relationship
with queen mary is the spark.

23:39.786 --> 23:42.720
Or are you innocent
of that, as well?

23:44.656 --> 23:46.657
If you think
there's truth to it,

23:46.659 --> 23:48.559
Then why entertain
my marriage offer?

23:49.828 --> 23:51.662
Because it doesn't matter.

23:51.664 --> 23:54.465
Elizabeth will not hold
this dalliance against you.

23:54.467 --> 23:57.768
Regardless, my queen's
interest is firm,

23:57.770 --> 24:00.671
So the decision is yours--
face your fate in France,

24:00.673 --> 24:02.873
Or seek elizabeth's
hand in marriage.

24:05.544 --> 24:08.446
In France, the only fate
left for me is a noose.

24:11.750 --> 24:14.185
I can leave
for England immediately

24:14.187 --> 24:16.020
So that elizabeth
may make her decision.

24:16.022 --> 24:17.888
Elizabeth's decision
is already made.

24:17.890 --> 24:19.590
She faces fierce and
immediate threats

24:19.592 --> 24:21.592
From those who want
a man on the throne.

24:21.594 --> 24:22.893
To stem these threats,

24:22.895 --> 24:25.563
Elizabeth intends to marry
as soon as possible.

24:25.565 --> 24:27.798
She desires
a foothold in France.

24:30.235 --> 24:34.705
Queen elizabeth accepts your
offer of marriage, prince condÃ©.

24:34.707 --> 24:37.942
You will be
king consort of England.

24:45.617 --> 24:47.651
â™ª all right, come close...

24:47.653 --> 24:49.787
You must be
the new girls.

24:49.789 --> 24:51.789
You're just in time--
