â™ª and I never knew

30:14.046 --> 30:17.815
â™ª if I'd be landing

30:20.385 --> 30:24.421
â™ª and I will run fast

30:24.423 --> 30:28.158
â™ª outlast everyone...

30:28.160 --> 30:29.993
I do.

30:29.995 --> 30:32.129
â™ª lasted

30:32.131 --> 30:36.233
â™ª no, oh, oh, oh, oh...

30:36.235 --> 30:39.269
Long live his majesty,
king louis of England.

30:40.305 --> 30:43.073
God save the king.

30:43.075 --> 30:47.477
â™ª all the king's horses
and all the king's men... â™ª

30:49.414 --> 30:52.316
Must be hard to sleep
on one's first night as a king.

30:54.252 --> 30:57.087
Lying next to a sharp
broadsword doesn't help either.

30:57.089 --> 30:59.289
It's tradition.

30:59.291 --> 31:01.925
We must sleep in the same bed
to consummate the marriage,

31:01.927 --> 31:04.194
But the sword is there
to guard the proxy

31:04.196 --> 31:06.163
From becoming
an actual wife.

31:07.365 --> 31:09.199
Does the proxy have a name?

31:09.201 --> 31:11.201
Annabelle breton.

31:12.570 --> 31:14.271
You're lord
breton's daughter?

31:15.573 --> 31:17.374
Your father's
a loyal french lord.

31:17.376 --> 31:19.910
How does his daughter come to be
the proxy of an english queen?

31:19.912 --> 31:22.079
My family is protestant.

31:22.081 --> 31:24.081
I was raised
in english court,

31:24.083 --> 31:26.316
But my heart has always
been with France.

31:26.318 --> 31:28.318
It must have been hard,

31:28.320 --> 31:31.355
Having to forsake
your home, your heart.

31:31.357 --> 31:33.357
It was.

31:33.359 --> 31:35.425
Will you be a good king?

31:37.095 --> 31:39.296
Will you bring
England and France,

31:39.298 --> 31:41.498
Catholic and protestant,
closer together?

31:41.500 --> 31:44.067
So that my family,
and families like mine,

31:44.069 --> 31:47.104
Can feel safe again in the land
that they were born to and love?

31:48.339 --> 31:50.507
I will do all I can...

31:50.509 --> 31:52.976
To be the king your family,

31:52.978 --> 31:55.479
England and France deserve.

31:57.248 --> 32:00.083
Are you eager
to meet her?

32:00.085 --> 32:01.385
Your wife.

32:01.387 --> 32:04.121
Elizabeth.

32:04.123 --> 32:06.189
Would you like me
to tell you about her?

32:06.191 --> 32:08.292
No. Not now.

32:08.294 --> 32:11.962
<i>Tonight, my head and my heart</i>

32:11.964 --> 32:13.597
<i>Are on the life, the people</i>

32:13.599 --> 32:16.466
<i>I leave behind.</i>

32:16.468 --> 32:19.303
Annabelle:
Will you miss France very much?

32:19.305 --> 32:22.339
I will miss her
with all my heart.

32:30.048 --> 32:32.015
Akers:
Dawn's first light

32:32.017 --> 32:33.283
Offers us an advantage--

32:33.285 --> 32:35.452
The road to the port
should be largely unoccupied.

32:35.454 --> 32:37.321
I won't feel safe until
we're aboard that ship

32:37.323 --> 32:38.722
And bound
for England.
Understandably.

32:38.724 --> 32:41.458
Queen elizabeth's
new king consort

32:41.460 --> 32:43.627
Would be a prize captive
for any frenchman.

32:43.629 --> 32:46.663
(bell tolling in distance)

32:46.665 --> 32:49.099
Whoa. Whoa.

32:49.101 --> 32:51.568
Conde: A fire.
It's coming from the village.

32:51.570 --> 32:54.004
The girl, annabelle--
she was still sleeping.

32:54.006 --> 32:55.339
Your majesty,
let me go.

32:55.341 --> 32:57.207
If it's the house, this may be
an attempt on your life.

32:57.209 --> 32:58.709
Wait for me here.

32:58.711 --> 32:59.977
(horse whinnies)

33:04.182 --> 33:07.117
(gentle music playing)

33:07.119 --> 33:09.720
General, your bravery
will not soon be forgotten.

33:09.722 --> 33:13.123
We owe you a great
debt of gratitude.

33:13.125 --> 33:14.725
Men and women: Cheers!
Man: Hear, hear!

33:14.727 --> 33:16.326
Lady kenna.

33:16.328 --> 33:17.260
I trust you enjoyed

33:17.262 --> 33:18.628
Your evening
in the village?

33:18.630 --> 33:20.163
I'm sorry?

33:20.165 --> 33:22.499
A queen's lady...
In a brothel.

33:22.501 --> 33:24.768
So you saw me.

33:24.770 --> 33:26.470
I did.

33:26.472 --> 33:29.272
I heard you were
enjoying your victory.

33:29.274 --> 33:31.675
That's quite the feat,
rescuing all those boys.

33:31.677 --> 33:33.276
Not all of them,
I'm afraid.

33:33.278 --> 33:35.345
One of my own men was lost,
as well.

33:35.347 --> 33:36.613
In the efforts to save
a very rich boy.

33:36.615 --> 33:39.383
I hope it was worth it.

33:39.385 --> 33:41.018
There was a choice
to be made,

33:41.020 --> 33:42.252
Between saving
the nobles' sons

33:42.254 --> 33:44.488
And the common boys.

33:44.490 --> 33:47.057
Either way,
someone would have died.

33:47.059 --> 33:48.759
And you chose...
The money.

33:48.761 --> 33:51.361
And the gratitude
of a very powerful man.

33:53.131 --> 33:55.599
I lost my son two years ago.

33:55.601 --> 33:59.770
He was taken captive
by enemy forces, and now...

33:59.772 --> 34:03.540
I wonder, every day:
Is he alive or dead?

34:03.542 --> 34:05.142
I'm sorry.

34:05.144 --> 34:06.543
Don't be.

34:06.545 --> 34:08.545
These things, they provide
a level of protection

34:08.547 --> 34:10.580
And I won't apologize

34:10.582 --> 34:12.516
For assuring my spot
above the fray.

34:13.418 --> 34:15.318
You're disappointed.

34:15.320 --> 34:16.753
A lady likes to think

34:16.755 --> 34:19.256
The protectors of the realm
are all willing

34:19.258 --> 34:21.358
To sacrifice themselves for--
a lofty cause

34:21.360 --> 34:22.793
Which has nothing
to do with them

34:22.795 --> 34:24.361
Or the people they care about.

34:24.363 --> 34:25.595
No.

34:25.597 --> 34:27.764
I understand the
need for protection.

34:27.766 --> 34:29.533
More so than most.

34:29.535 --> 34:33.170
Your husband showed
great valor in the raid.

34:33.172 --> 34:36.239
I invited him
to join us at the...

34:36.241 --> 34:38.341
Celebration of my exploits.

34:38.343 --> 34:40.477
But he mentioned a woman,

34:40.479 --> 34:42.612
Someone waiting for him.

34:42.614 --> 34:44.147
On the road back,

34:44.149 --> 34:45.449
I watched him peel away
into the woods.

34:46.784 --> 34:49.186
I was pleased
the woman wasn't you.

34:49.188 --> 34:50.620
Why?

34:50.622 --> 34:54.558
I may look out for myself,
lady kenna...

34:54.560 --> 34:57.194
But I don't take things
that don't belong to me.

34:57.196 --> 34:59.463
And it sounds like you

34:59.465 --> 35:01.565
Don't belong to anyone.

35:06.838 --> 35:08.505
(sighs)

35:22.386 --> 35:23.587
Annabelle is dead.

35:23.589 --> 35:25.188
The priest that
performed your wedding

35:25.190 --> 35:26.523
Has been murdered.

35:26.525 --> 35:28.758
And every last document
signifying your union

35:28.760 --> 35:30.827
Has been destroyed.

35:30.829 --> 35:32.362
It seems that someone
is out to erase

35:32.364 --> 35:33.763
All evidence of your wedding,
prince condÃ©.

35:33.765 --> 35:36.566
They've undone the wedding.

35:36.568 --> 35:39.536
We can marry again.
Find another proxy.

35:39.538 --> 35:41.238
I'm afraid that's not
a decision I can make

35:41.240 --> 35:42.372
Without first
consulting my queen.

35:42.374 --> 35:43.607
Who would do this?

35:43.609 --> 35:45.242
Why?

35:45.244 --> 35:46.409
An alliance
between England

35:46.411 --> 35:48.278
And protestant France
threatens many.

35:48.280 --> 35:49.579
I would look first
to the french crown

35:49.581 --> 35:51.515
And then to any of
elizabeth's foes abroad.

35:51.517 --> 35:53.150
This was a careful choice--

35:53.152 --> 35:55.318
Killing the marriage
while saving me.

35:55.320 --> 35:56.786
Well, only one of you needed
to die to sever the contract.

35:56.788 --> 35:58.255
Annabelle is a woman,
while you are

35:58.257 --> 35:59.523
Brother to the king of navarre.

35:59.525 --> 36:02.225
A protestant king
with ties to England.

36:04.462 --> 36:06.663
Maybe it wasn't a foe at all,
but elizabeth herself.

36:06.665 --> 36:08.498
Perhaps she simply

36:08.500 --> 36:09.833
Changed her mind about
marrying me, and didn't want

36:09.835 --> 36:11.368
To kill me and risk
her alliance with navarre.

36:11.370 --> 36:14.504
If I'm wrong,
take me to England.

36:14.506 --> 36:16.406
I will wed elizabeth,
standing by her side.

36:16.408 --> 36:17.941
I can't do that.

36:17.943 --> 36:19.476
Even if the valois
didn't set the fire,

36:19.478 --> 36:20.510
They will find out
what I did soon.

36:20.512 --> 36:21.878
Marrying elizabeth is treason.

36:21.880 --> 36:24.314
You said yourself
it was a great risk.

36:24.316 --> 36:26.349
I turned my back on mary!

36:26.351 --> 36:28.351
Betrayed my allies in France!

36:28.353 --> 36:29.486
All for elizabeth!

36:29.488 --> 36:30.687
Certainly she owes me something!

36:30.689 --> 36:32.222
I don't think her majesty

36:32.224 --> 36:33.557
Would see it that way.

36:41.699 --> 36:43.200
Narcisse:
Word of condÃ©'s involvement

36:43.202 --> 36:44.668
With the radicals
has spread nicely.

36:44.670 --> 36:46.836
But it appears that
I underestimated

36:46.838 --> 36:48.271
The sway that mary

36:48.273 --> 36:50.373
Still holds over your son.

36:50.375 --> 36:52.709
I hear francis
is unconvinced

36:52.711 --> 36:54.878
Of his guilt.
That doesn't
matter anymore.

36:54.880 --> 36:56.479
You won't believe
what condÃ©'s done.

36:57.782 --> 37:00.517
Married the queen of England.

37:00.519 --> 37:01.818
By proxy.

37:01.820 --> 37:03.420
A girl known
to be a member

37:03.422 --> 37:04.955
Of elizabeth's inner circle.

37:04.957 --> 37:07.958
A broadsword was found in
the bed that they shared.

37:07.960 --> 37:09.726
My god.

37:10.895 --> 37:13.797
How do you know this?
There was a fire.

37:13.799 --> 37:16.800
She died. Someone was trying
to erase all legal proof,

37:16.802 --> 37:18.802
But there were
witnesses.

37:18.804 --> 37:20.804
CondÃ© was identified
as one of the newlyweds

37:20.806 --> 37:22.839
At a borrowed noble's house.

37:22.841 --> 37:24.007
Were they successful?

37:24.009 --> 37:26.643
Or is condÃ©
now the king of England?

37:26.645 --> 37:27.877
I don't know.

37:27.879 --> 37:29.813
He fled.

37:29.815 --> 37:31.915
If condÃ© and
elizabeth are married,

37:31.917 --> 37:34.784
Then she has essentially
laid claim to France.

37:34.786 --> 37:36.886
She'll rally the
protestants here,

37:36.888 --> 37:38.822
A french king at her side.

37:38.824 --> 37:40.357
I am well aware.

37:43.694 --> 37:47.831
Did you do this, catherine?

37:47.833 --> 37:49.799
Learn of the wedding

37:49.801 --> 37:51.568
And then have it undone?

37:51.570 --> 37:52.902
No!

37:52.904 --> 37:54.304
Did you,

37:54.306 --> 37:55.572
In some way?

37:55.574 --> 37:56.840
Oh, when tying condÃ©
to the assault

37:56.842 --> 37:58.375
On the monastery wasn't enough?

37:59.877 --> 38:01.378
Maybe you're asking me

38:01.380 --> 38:03.313
To throw suspicion off yourself.

38:03.315 --> 38:06.316
No. But this has a
breadth and a scope

38:06.318 --> 38:07.751
That our plan did not.

38:07.753 --> 38:10.453
This will ruin condÃ©
in France forever.

38:11.989 --> 38:15.292
Is this how it's going to be
from now on?

38:15.294 --> 38:16.960
Both of us constantly

38:16.962 --> 38:19.329
Wondering what
the other is up to?

38:19.331 --> 38:20.864
Yes.

38:20.866 --> 38:22.465
You have met your match.

38:22.467 --> 38:24.434
(sighs)

38:24.436 --> 38:25.669
This is terrible news...
(wry laugh)

38:25.671 --> 38:26.970
...But there is something

38:26.972 --> 38:28.505
Marvelous in that,

38:28.507 --> 38:29.939
Wouldn't you say?

38:29.941 --> 38:31.041
Yeah.

38:32.910 --> 38:35.745
(wind whistling)

38:35.747 --> 38:37.480
What do you have to report?

38:37.482 --> 38:38.915
Lord narcisse

38:38.917 --> 38:40.850
Was seen in the village
last night.
Hmm.

38:40.852 --> 38:42.919
Outside a brothel.

38:42.921 --> 38:44.521
Well, did he go inside?

38:44.523 --> 38:46.356
He never entered
the establishment.

38:46.358 --> 38:47.991
Hmm.
He was merely detained

38:47.993 --> 38:49.059
By a conversation

38:49.061 --> 38:50.660
With lady lola.

38:50.662 --> 38:52.028
Lady lola?

38:52.030 --> 38:53.963
Some time together in the past.

38:53.965 --> 38:55.965
And their exchange this night?

38:55.967 --> 38:57.367
Mere words.

38:57.369 --> 38:59.369
A matter of minutes
and they moved on.

38:59.371 --> 39:00.970
Did they meet again?

39:00.972 --> 39:02.405
No.

39:04.875 --> 39:07.577
And the tenor of their exchange?

39:09.847 --> 39:11.014
Edmond?

39:11.016 --> 39:12.682
Tell me this:

39:12.684 --> 39:14.751
If lady lola were your wife

39:14.753 --> 39:16.553
And you spied her

39:16.555 --> 39:19.589
In an identical encounter

39:19.591 --> 39:22.625
With lord narcisse,

39:22.627 --> 39:24.060
How would you feel?

39:24.062 --> 39:26.996
If it were my wife...

39:28.599 --> 39:29.933
...I'd want him dead.

39:32.002 --> 39:33.603
Thank you for your candor.

39:38.876 --> 39:41.144
(door opens, closes)

39:42.947 --> 39:45.615
Married?

39:45.617 --> 39:47.117
To elizabeth?

39:48.452 --> 39:50.653
It's not true.
It is.

39:50.655 --> 39:52.055
Or was, for however long

39:52.057 --> 39:53.957
Their marriage
may have lasted.

39:53.959 --> 39:55.959
No one knows if the arson
and murders undid their union,

39:55.961 --> 39:57.994
Or if condÃ©

39:57.996 --> 40:00.563
Fled France
king consort of England.

40:03.134 --> 40:04.934
Louis was approached

40:04.936 --> 40:07.670
By elizabeth's envoy
some weeks ago.

40:08.939 --> 40:10.106
He told me so himself.

40:10.108 --> 40:11.975
You knew about this?

40:11.977 --> 40:14.010
That condÃ© was courting England?

40:14.012 --> 40:15.412
Our greatest enemy--

40:15.414 --> 40:17.514
<i>Your</i> greatest enemy?

40:17.516 --> 40:19.516
He swore to me that he would
reject her proposal.

40:19.518 --> 40:20.950
And you believed him.

40:20.952 --> 40:22.585
If he did this,
it's only because

40:22.587 --> 40:24.454
He felt he had no other choice.

40:24.456 --> 40:26.022
I abandoned him.

40:26.024 --> 40:27.424
I sent troops
to scotland for you--

40:27.426 --> 40:28.658
To honor your needs,

40:28.660 --> 40:30.126
Your nation's needs.

40:30.128 --> 40:32.061
And still, you choose
to lie to me.

40:32.063 --> 40:34.130
There were things
I could not share with you.

40:34.132 --> 40:36.466
Or that condÃ©
couldn't share with me.

40:36.468 --> 40:40.036
But he has done this, francis,
because I ended things.

40:41.639 --> 40:43.173
It's over between us.

40:43.175 --> 40:46.142
I honored
my loyalty to France.

40:46.144 --> 40:48.945
I chose to stand by my husband.

40:48.947 --> 40:50.013
As your queen, if not your wife.

40:50.015 --> 40:53.116
An important distinction.

40:53.118 --> 40:55.118
I came back to do
the right thing.

40:55.120 --> 40:57.053
Just as I am trying to do now,

40:57.055 --> 40:58.688
By telling you the truth
about condÃ©.

40:58.690 --> 41:00.457
Am I supposed
to thank you for this?

41:01.959 --> 41:04.027
Yes, you did do the right thing,
mary, politically.

41:05.029 --> 41:06.463
Staying in France,

41:06.465 --> 41:08.631
Staying with me,
secures the alliance

41:08.633 --> 41:10.066
And your throne in scotland.

41:10.068 --> 41:11.468
That's not the only reason...

41:11.470 --> 41:14.037
Which makes you no
different from condÃ©.

41:14.039 --> 41:16.473
He chose elizabeth
for the same reason:

41:16.475 --> 41:18.475
To secure a political future.

41:18.477 --> 41:21.077
And now we will suffer
the consequences.

41:21.079 --> 41:23.213
If elizabeth has
a stronghold in France

41:23.215 --> 41:25.482
And condÃ©'s claim
to the throne...

41:25.484 --> 41:28.051
This may mean
the end of our reign.

